    {
      "id": "3ea2a4a112a235125f2ce333741a1cc4c176192b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-15 13:55:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I'm not sure I understand the requirement for this patch.\n\nJust to work around some poorly though out semantics for these proc params so that we can get on with Lustre development. I think this should go ahead and the proc param handlers can be fixed in a subsequent patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bbca06302ce5409eef6c674549177ff02d1f30fa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-16 13:24:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe brw_size param has not yet been included in a release. Since it used lprocfs_write_helper() it ignored any suffix that was used:\n\n \nt:lustre# lctl get_param obdfilter.*.brw_size\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=1\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=1\nt:lustre# lctl set_param obdfilter.*.brw_size=16\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=16\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=16\nt:lustre# lctl get_param obdfilter.*.brw_size\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=16\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=16\nt:lustre# lctl set_param obdfilter.*.brw_size=16K\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=16K\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=16K\nt:lustre# lctl get_param obdfilter.*.brw_size\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=16\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=16\nt:lustre# lctl set_param obdfilter.*.brw_size=16M\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=16M\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=16M\nt:lustre# lctl get_param obdfilter.*.brw_size\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0000.brw_size=16\nobdfilter.lustre-OST0001.brw_size=16",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a7bcfbb755b56462b159a6f4dedbc51acc730f88",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-16 18:44:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI agree that brw_size was only landed to master in 2.8+, but DDN was previously using it.  In any case, max_pages_per_rpc has been around for ages, and it has accepted arguments of the form \"4M\" for a long time.\n\nI agree the parameter name was ill chosen, since it directly reflects the internal implementation of the code.  The problem is that specifying the RPC size in terms of client PAGE_SIZE depends on what PAGE_SIZE is, and that may differ between clients.  The ability to uniformly specify the RPC size in units of MB was added after the fact.  \n\nWhile I agree this is baggage we'd all prefer wasn't there, breaking this tunable (which is one that is changed quite frequently) would be even worse.  I've submitted a patch to disable this test, which should have been done on Friday, and Oleg is working on a patch to fix the actual parsing of this parameter so that it allows units as it previously did.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c2816e0ef0ce581dabf884880b3f25bb8859c996",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-16 20:42:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt's fine to fix the param handlers, but this change is correct and landing it is better than disabling the test.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c5a3f83a62fcd960a6f1e904e93f228483c40e2b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-17 01:39:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDefinitely the brw_size part of the patch is correct, and it should be landed.  The max_pages_per_rpc part of the fix is not incorrect.  There was pre-existing behaviour of this tunable with specified units that was not being tested, and I'm reluctant to remove the one place that is currently testing the behaviour as it was before the http://review.whamcloud.com/16930 patch landed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ab9b450c4f4a5aca01f6f1cd4ba46540a50c05d9",
